{"GAIDIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to hypogeic acid; -- applied to an acid obtained from hypogeic acid.","pos":""}],"GAILLARD":[{"def":"Gay; brisk; merry; galliard.","pos":""}],"GAILLIARDE":[{"def":"A lively French and Italian dance.","pos":""}],"GAILY":[{"def":"Merrily; showily.","pos":""}],"GAIN":[{"def":"A square or beveled notch cut out of a girder, binding joist, or other timber which supports a floor beam, so as to receive the end of the floor beam.","pos":""}],"GAINABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being obtained or reached.","pos":""}],"GAINFUL":[{"def":"Profitable; advantageous; lucrative.","pos":""}],"GAINLESS":[{"def":"Not producing gain; unprofitable.","pos":""}],"GAINLY":[{"def":"Handily; readily; dexterously; advantageously.","pos":""}],"GAINPAIN":[{"def":"Bread-gainer; -- a term applied in the Middle Ages to the sword of a hired soldier.","pos":"noun"}],"GAINSAY":[{"def":"To contradict; to deny; to controvert; to dispute; to forbid.","pos":""}],"GAINSAYER":[{"def":"One who gainsays, contradicts, or denies.","pos":""}],"GAINSBOROUGH HAT":[{"def":"A woman's broad-brimmed hat of a form thought to resemble those shown in portraits by Thomas Gainsborough, the English artist (1727- 88).","pos":""}],"GAINSOME":[{"def":"A contraction of Against.","pos":""}],"GAINSTAND":[{"def":"To withstand; to resist.","pos":""}],"GAINSTRIVE":[{"def":"To strive or struggle against; to withstand.","pos":""}],"GAIRFOWL":[{"def":"Same as Garish, Garishly, Garishness.","pos":""}],"GAIT":[{"def":"A going; a walk; a march; a way.","pos":""},{"def":"Manner of walking or stepping; bearing or carriage while moving.","pos":""}],"GAITED":[{"def":"Having (such) a gait; -- used in composition; as, slow-gaited; heavy-gaited.","pos":""}],"GAITER":[{"def":"A covering of cloth or leather for the ankle and instep, or for the whole leg from the knee to the instep, fitting down upon the shoe.","pos":""},{"def":"A kind of shoe, consisting of cloth, and covering the ankle.","pos":""}]}